16 (A) ON OR BEFORE DECEMBER 31, 2025, THE PROGRAM SHALL ESTABLISH
17 AND MAINTAIN AN ONLINE REGISTRY TO PROVIDE INFORMATION TO REGISTERED
18 INDIVIDUALS.
19 (B) THE REGISTRY SHALL:
20 (1) ALLOW AN INDIVIDUAL TO REGISTER;
21 (2) PROVIDE REGISTERED INDIVIDUALS INFORMATION, INCLUDING
22 AVAILABLE SERVICES, BENEFITS, AND NEWS THAT IMPACTS VETERANS, SERVICE
23 MEMBERS, MILITARY FAMILIES, AND OTHER INTERESTED INDIVIDUALS;
24 (3) ALLOW A REGISTERED INDIVIDUAL TO UPDATE THEIR ONLINE
25 REGISTRY INFORMATION INCLUDING THE INDIVIDUAL’S NAME, E–MAIL ADDRESS,
26 AND OPTIONAL STATUSES; AND
27 (4) HAVE THE CAPABILITY TO IMPORT SHAREABLE REGISTRATION
28 DATA PROVIDED BY OTHER AUTHORIZED UNITS OF STATE GOVERNMENT.
29 (C) THE PROGRAM:
30 (1) SHALL REQUIRE AN INDIVIDUAL REGISTERING WITH THE ONLINE
31 REGISTRY TO PROVIDE THE INDIVIDUAL’S NAME AND EMAIL ADDRESS; AND

